profile_positions.description:
Provided E2E Finance advice and managed full P&L for the Chemicals Solvents business in Europe, the Middle East & Africa (±$1bln sales; >$100mln margin), particularly in the areas of contracting, strategy, planning & appraisal, latest estimates, business performance and risk management, economic evaluation and Management Information reporting.

• Finance lead in the EUAFME Solvents Regional Leadership Team;
• Provided high-value finance advice and steer for commercial contracts, mandates, negotiations, evaluating for profitability and risk exposure. Helped shape the contracting strategy by providing insights in the contract portfolio’s price exposures and articulated the value of portfolio changes;
• Granted finance advice on Base Chemicals Investment Projects by providing economic valuation and financial and business insights to ensure robust and economically sound investment proposals;
• Led the annual Business Planning process and ensured alignment between all stakeholders;
• Led the financial reporting, monthly business performance management and timely delivery of accurate MI and recommendations to drive commercial decision making and optimization;
• Identified and articulated key value levers, and the impact of dynamic business and market variables, risks and exposures to the business’ profitability and cash generation;
• Successfully onboarded, effectively integrated & managed staff (dotted line) in Finance Operations, recognized as best-in-class, setting the team up for success to provide high-valued finance support to a wide range of business stakeholders, instilling a culture of full accountability for their delivery;

Finance Lead to coordinate the Moerdijk Manufacturing Site Performance Unit Review.

• Created and coordinated Moerdijk Business Performance Unit Review Appraisal pack ensuring alignment across technical Manufacturing and commercial Chemicals senior stakeholders;
• Quickly built effective working relationship with site leadership ensuring high quality and on-time delivery;
• Managed workload on top of normal job (as Finance Advisor Chemicals) and prioritized activities very effectively.

Initiated and developed New Fuels investment proposal and roll-out plan, leading to the FID and installation of several (25 in 2018) electrical charge points on Shell Retail sites in NL and the FID for 4 NL hydrogen sites in 2020. As front-runner in the Energy Transition in Retail NL, managed to shift mindset across senior stakeholders & business to adopt change.

• Aligned and challenged targets of New Fuels business development teams with Shell Group Strategy forecasts, market demand feasibility (e.g. car availability) and consumer preference;
• Identified potential scenarios for NL Retail and B2B market development and impact on pathways;
• Provided finance input and earned seat at the table in Decision Review Board meetings.

Provided economic valuation and investment advice across all segments of Retail in BeNeLux and France: marketing, network (>800 retail stations), sales & convenience retail for >200 Investment Proposals (with each an NPV $200k-10mln).

• Conducted full valuation of prospect acquisition or divestment sites, lease renewals, and Motorway tenders to set mandates and actual bid amounts;
• Played pivotal role in the preparation of the NL Motorway auction with a successful result: defending Shell sites successfully and acquiring a competitor site, securing a total NPV of $20mln, and sold one site delivering significant incremental value to Shell vs. own operation; 
• Conducted Post Investment Reviews on acquired sites, new store concepts & marketing promotions;
• Earned seat at the table in negotiations with third party partners/suppliers by conducting sound economic valuations to ensure financial sensibility of deal (e.g. Starbucks Self-Serve & Selecta);
• Conducted profitability study on Dealer Owned platform, helping the business team understand the implications of various Dealer Strategies and contract terms and advised improvements;
• Remodeled Retail Valuation Model for four countries, incorporating new assumptions and forecasts on long-term outlook of volumes and margin trends, while ensuring continuous improvement and alignment with site P&L. Successful stakeholder management and persistent focus on delivery, ensured timely roll-out for first time in years despite adverse circumstances;
• Provided well received Economic Analysis and Valuation training to new Retail staff;
• Acted as Retail Economics Manager during 2-month absence of incumbent while managing work load and prioritizing activities very effectively.

Provided Finance, Planning & Appraisal (FP&A) support to the Global Wells business as highly valued Business Partner.

• Managed the Global Planning, Reporting and Latest Estimates processes ensuring timely and high-quality submissions by setting clear direction and leading the regional finance teams in Americas, Europe, Africa & Asia through these processes;
• Coordinated and prepared the Quarterly Business Performance Appraisals for direct review by EVP Wells, EVP P&T Finance and the P&T Director;
• Provided high-quality Management Information for the Global Wells business, Global Wells Finance function, and direct MI and budgeting support to the P&T Wells Safety VP and GMs;
• Managed improvement project to reduce unallocated expenses, travel costs and unbillable working hours, ensuring cost recovery from end-customers (Upstream OUs/JV partners), driving value through analytical insights;
• Functioned successfully as Risk Management focal point and Ethics and Compliance champion.

Developed end-to-end process documentation tool as a one-stop-shop for process guidelines, best practices, policies and financial controls to ensure knowledge sharing, use of best practices, and streamlining of Order to Cash, Requisition to Pay, Project set-up and Time Writing processes;

• Guided the IT-team and managed timely development of end-user’s website-interface;
• Effective change management and stakeholder engagement ensured project and roll-out success.

